Incident.Summary: The victim who has an active protective order against her father was threatened by him through a letter.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText:
This incident was captured on body-worn camera/In-car camera not activated.
Scene Processing:
     The victim provided me with one (1) four-page letter with the below referenced threats. The Victim completed one (1) Maryland State Police Written Statement (MSP Form 076), which is attached to this report. I received one (1) copy of a final protective order.
Physical Evidence:
-One (1) four-page handwritten letter.
-One (1) Maryland State Police Written Statement (MSP Form 076)
-One (1) copy of a Final Protective Order.
Narrative:
     On 05/31/2023 at approximately 1500 hours, I responded to the Maryland State Police Leonardtown Barrack for a reported violation of a protective order. Upon my arrival, I made contact with the victim, Breann Nicole Virts (W/F DOB: 08/06/2004), who advised she has an active protective order against her father, Paul Ashcom Virts (W/M DOB:12/07/1968), and had received a letter in which he threatens her. Breann advised on the evening of 05/30/2023, her grandmother Nancy Lucretia Virts (W/F DOB: 01/03/1936), provided her with a letter her father had written to Nancy in February 2023. Nancy advised Breann the contents of the letter were worrying, which was why she provided her the letter. Breann advised she did not look at the letter until 05/31/2023, during which time she became in fear for her life due to threats Paul had made in the letter towards herself and her fiancé, Kaiden Seth Uber. Breann had the actual letter with her at the time and provided it to me. Breann advised Paul is currently incarcerated at Western Correctional Facility.
     The letter which is dated 02/07/2023 states Paul attempted to call Nancy at approximately 2000 hours, at which time Kaiden answered the phone and told him not to call again. In the letter, Paul threatens Kaiden several times advising if he keeps playing with Nancy’s phone he is going to send MS-13 to his parents address, and then lists Kaidens actual parents address of 9817 Emerald Lane, Newberg, Maryland, 20664. Paul states in the letter he does not want Nancy speaking on the phone with him on speaker phone so Breann can listen, he advises if it happens he will send MS-13 to 29350 Trent Hall Road, Mechanicsville, MD, 20659, 27170 Barton Street, Mechanicsville, MD, 20659 and 115 Pequeno Road, Albuquerque, New Mexico where Breann’s cousin Hannah lives.  Paul continues to state Breann and Kaiden better not be living at the Barton Street house as he wants to live there when he is released. He states Kaiden should not try to control Nancy’s household as he’ll have his parents “touched’ by MS-13. He continues to advise he knows the leader of MS-13 on the west coast, the president of the Hells Angels, who he advises he has known for 17 years. He continues to state he has been in contact with a “Mr. Talton”, who he advises is in the mafia. He advises Nancy to get Breann and Kaiden out of the house or he knows someone who will personally remove them from the house. Paul continues to state Breann messed up by lying to get the “peace order”, and he is going to “beat the shit out of Breann’s boyfriend Kaiden." He goes on to state in the past 17 years he has learned to fight and he is not afraid to stab someone if he has to. He goes on to state “Friends of mine outside these walls are aware of Kaiden’s parent’s address I put them on point just in case he wants to play games with my family.” He advises he is going to write a letter to Kaiden’s parents and had “Marty” from the Hells Angels reach out and touch someone from inside these walls.  He goes on to state he got new tattoos of a swastika, 14/88 and white pride tattooed on him. He goes on to state all hell will break loose if Kaiden and Breann live at the Barton Street house. He continues to state if Kaiden and Breann go back to the Barton Street house they will receive a visit from MS-13.
     Breann advised the letter is one of many, including multiple phone calls in which Paul threatens to kill her. Breann advised Nancy received another letter in April from Paul which Nancy destroyed. Breann advised in this letter Paul threatens to send MS-13 to her residence if she does not drive Nancy to visit Paul. When asked how she believes these threats are credible, Breann advised she believes Paul is a member of the Aryan Brotherhood. Breanna advise she was made aware of Paul’s ties to MS-13 through her Aunt Theresa. Breann advised Theresa knows several people Paul is incarcerated with, who advised her of his ties to MS-13. Breann stated the ties to MS-13 came from a dispute he had with members of 18th Street. Breann advised in February or March of 2023, she was contacted by someone with the Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI) Baltimore Field Office referencing threats made to her, her sister ( Hannah Lynn Virts (W/F DOB:09/24/2002), and Kaiden utilizing her address. Breann advised she was told the threats were picked up through “phone chatter” from members of MS-13.
     Breann advised she believes previously Paul has sent people to break into her residence after an argument, which she reported to Tpr. Hersh #7443 (Case # 22-MSP-046292). Breann advised the evening of the burglary, Paul contacted her advising her room was dirty. Breann advised she has been in contact with Kaiden’s mother, Dorothy Ellen Manning, who advised she recently has had suspicious vehicles driving past her residence.
     Breann stated due to continuous threats and harassment from paul, she applied for and received a Final Protective Order from the St. Mary’s County District Court. The protective order was granted and is valid through 11/29/2023. The order states Paul Virts shall not abuse, threaten to abuse Breann Virts, and he shall not contact, attempt to contact, or harass (in person, by telephone, in writing, or by any other means). I received a copy of the final protective order from the St. Mary’s County Sheriffs Office, which is attached to this report. Breann completed a Maryland State Police Written Statement (MSP Form 076) which is attached to this report. A copy of all paperwork is attached to this report. Breann states the letter has put her in fear for her life, Kaidens life and his parents. Pauls Virts currently has four open cases for violating the protective order, harassment and telephone misuse against Breann.
     On 05/31/2023, I contacted Assistant States Attorney A. Mosier by email referencing charges for this case.
I request this case remain open pending further investigation and charging.
All events occurred in St. Mary’s County, Maryland.
